title: Did Ari Fleischer compare his identity to be refined by voter identification laws?
subtitle: The tweeting of the former White House press secretary apples to Orange Garnett are two unrelated things.
author: Bethania Palma
vclaim: The former White House Press Secretary, Ari Fletcher, said that showing identity when a COVID-19 vaccine was obtained in New York was "feeling" just like the voter identity laws that Republican legislators pressured.
